main ISOLATION
means if more than 1 transation happens concurrently how system keeps them seperate to produce output
there are 4 main isolation levels: suppose 2 transations are happening simultaneously
-> repeatable reads
    -> whatever is the value in the table on first read will remain as it is untill the transation ends. does not have a impact of other transations updating that value
-> read commit 
    -> if t2 commits the next read of t1 will get a updated value
-> read uncommit
    -> if t2 just updates without commiting t1 will still get that updated value on read but if t1 rolled back instead of commit then that would be a dirty read for t1
-> serializable  
    -> if t1 starts a read then t2 gets blocked for write of that row untill t1 commit or rollback, or if t1 starts writing t2 gets blocked on reading and writing untill commit
    or rollback.

