Queuing
A Major usecase of queuing is doing task concurrently, that could be achieved by multithreading then why queuing is requied as it will have low latency?
-> As suppose we have hundreds of task to be executed we can't assign each task to one thread as there is a limit, so we have to make a schedular and have a buffer that holds
the task, queuing not only provides this out of the box but also decouples the system as this schedular can be on different machine and instead of thread of the same machine
 we have consumers that run on differnt machine. which make it fault tolerant also.
Message queues

for async processing queues are generally used cosumers pull the message do the processing and then delete message from queue, if the message is not deleted due to some failure 
that message is again consumed by some consumer then will be deleted, so we have to be ok for processing it again or have dedupe check.

But the problem here is suppose on publishing a message in queue consumer have to do 2 tasks if task one suceeds but second fails then eaither we will get inconsistent state if we 
delete the message or we will have to do the first again if we choose to consume message again,
if we argue to make 2 queues for these 2 diff task then it might be the publishing in 1 got successful but 2nd got unsuccessful due to some failure as we are keeping publishing as 
sync task only, so to solve this message streams comes into picture.

Message streams

here the message streams is also a queue but with different set of consumers that are watching over it by iterating over the messages to consume them and keeping the offset of
consumed messages, messages of this queue are not deleted because diff consumer would be having different offset. Now this would solve the above problem.


Kafka as a Queuing mechanism
-> producers produce message with topics
    -> messages are like [headers, key, value, timestamp]
-> kafka brokers or servers (multiple brokers form kafka cluster) can have multiple partitions (phisical divisions) each partitian belongs to a topic (logical division) 
    for a topic lets suppose we have 3 partitians [p0,p1,p2] they can have there replica partitians across different brokers [to keep system running if broker dies]
    each partitian have one leader on a broker read and write happens on leader replicas are just for fault tolerance. Kafka have a mapping between partitian and broker to
    route message.[Key of meesage gets hashed to find partitian through mapping broker could be found.]
-> if a consumer group has subscribed to a topic then one partitian in a broker would only be consumed by one consumer in a consumer group, that consumer can consume different
    partitians even from different topics, in different consumer groups that same partitian can be consumed by some consumer. but for a same consumer group no 2 consumer can
    consume same partitian.
-> partitian for a topic decide how much parallely we want data to be consumed within a consumer group.


