Bloom filter

this is a DS used by recommendation engins, suppose recommendation engine provide a list of videos for a user but no one wants to see the videos that they have alreay watched so
simply we can keep a set of all watched video ids and check if something is already watched just don't recommend that, but that is not space efficient as data grows 

so one observation is if somebody have watched something it can't be unwatched so we can use that 

we are using stream of bits as a hash map 
so we can hash video Id by the size of bloom filter and make that bit 1 whenever we want to check if a video is watched we can check that bit, if that is off that means 100% that
video is not watched but if that is on then we are not sure if that is watched so we can discard that from recommending, so yeah bloom filters give false positive some times
but have high performance. we can decide the size of bloom filters by a formula that would be based on the keys that we are ingesting and false positive rates that we can tolerate.

